title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1971-12-31
lineage: Dat (Sony PCM-R500) > Tascam DA-3000 (16-bit/48k) > Adobe Audition CC2015 >Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/
description:
Set 1

Dancin' In The Streets, Mr. Charlie, Brown Eyed Women, Beat It On Down The Line, You Win Again, Jack Straw, Sugaree, El Paso, Chinatown Shuffle, Tennessee Jed, Mexicali Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Next Time You See Me, Playin' In The Band, Loser, One More Saturday Night*

Set 2

Truckin'-> Drums-> The Other One-> Me & My Uncle-> The Other One, Jam-> Black Peter, Big River, The Same Thing, Ramble On Rose, Sugar Magnolia, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E: Casey Jones

With Donna Godchaux * FM broadcast KSAN-San Francisco - Other artist(s): GD; NRPS; Yogi Phlegm

reviews.review_text:
Don't expect no help at all This is the California preview of Europe 72
Dancin' unsettled with some ill advised grandstanding 
but a generous 17 songs.
Donna Jean making her 1st appearance.
via Saturday Night.
I don't underestimate the power of her moxy!
The hard work and endless campus and small venue touring of 1971 delivers major dividends in 1972 when for a brief time you have Pigpen with Keith  sharing the stage with the greatest rock n roll quartet of the 1970's-- perhaps ever..

Better still! This is the best upgrade to this show I'm aware of and It's a beaut. It's lacking Weir's J. Edgar Hoover rap after Dancing...but you can find it on one of the other versions. The annoying hum seems completely gone and the vocals are full-bodied. They no longer sound like they're in a drain pipe. Thanks so much for the hard work.
- One of the best NYE shows you'll ever hear.
Great Show Hey, this one is awesome... LOL Did anyone catch what Bob was saying about someone wearing a diaper?? Hahahaa
Significant Upgrade Available If March ‘71 and May ‘72 got married and had a baby it would sound like this show. Look below for gd1971-12-31.142681.sb-d.miller.flac1648. It’s the one you want!

Thanks. I just wanted to thank everyone that made this show listenable!!! So far I'm enjoying it very much & I'm not finished listening to the First Set. A New Years Eve show that has Keith & Pigpen plus Donna's first appearance. Bobby even introduced Keith as "our new piano player". So that in itself says a lot about this show. And from what I've heard & read this version is a lot better than a lot of other versions of this show. Many many thanks to those that went thru the trouble of making this version the best it could be. And now I want to hear the resta of it.
Wow, I just listened to "Next Time You See Me". To be honest I've never been a big fan of that song. But the guitar work that Jerry puts into this version just convinced me to enjoy it. Cuz some of that song he's throwing down!!
